Islington South & Finsbury Labour Party Facebook Group Code of Conduct

The Islington South & Finsbury Labour Party is a private group (known to Facebook as a secret group) made up of Islington South & Finsbury Labour Party members and affiliated and registered supporters.

The purpose of this Code of Conduct is to ensure all participants are aware of the conduct expected of them and that they may expect from others. Please read it carefully.

A safe space for debate:

The aim of the group is to provide a space in which we encourage debate and participation. The Labour Party is a broad church and Islington South & Finsbury as a community is a model of tolerance and mutual respect. Our Facebook group should reflect this. We want this to be a safe space for members to air their views and opinions; all members are equal and are entitled to equal respect. To achieve this all members are urged to do the following:

*Help to create a constructive and pleasant environment for debate

*Treat all people with respect, fairly and equally

*Allow other members to express themselves

*Challenge constructively

*Be truthful and honest

*Remember you are representing the Labour Party to other members, especially new members to the party and group 

*Keep your posts relevant to politics, Islington South & Finsbury and/or the Labour Party


Unacceptable behaviour - Principles:

*Debate must relate to the person’s arguments and behaviours, not the person themselves. A person’s race, religion, age, disability, sexuality, gender or sexual identity, or any other identifying characteristic, must not be criticised or attacked in any way. Racist (that includes anti-Semitism, Islamophobia etc.), sexist, ageist, homophobic or any other kind of intolerant behaviour or language is not permitted

*No personal abuse, bullying, harassment, intimidation or aggressive behaviour or language 

*No propaganda for other parties

*No coordinated attacks, trolling, spamming or intentionally divisive comments or posts

*Posting personal information about other group members is not permitted

*Do not question the party loyalty or legitimacy of those who disagree with you

*Do not post conspiracy theories or unsourced stories or accusations

*Do not repeatedly post the same article

*Do not post screenshots of private discussions in the group or attack the group or Islington South & Finsbury Labour Party elsewhere on the internet, such as twitter or other FB groups. This is a closed FB group to debate issues within our broad church and as such is private.

*Do not block Admins

Summary:

People will disagree on many issues, but that is the foundation of debate. Remain respectful of other forum members so that everyone can enjoy the group. 

We have more in common than what divides us!

Community Learning Partnership is a charity, based at St Martin's Church, Muirfield Road,South Oxhey, Watford, WD19 6JD. Our sewing cafe is a new venture.
The idea is that you book in advance for one of our fortnightly sessions and use our sewing machines and equipment to produce your sewing projects.
These are not taught sessions, rather a chance to join fellow enthusiasts to complete projects you are working on already, or would like to begin.
Each month, there will be the chance to complete a group project. A written tutorial will be sourced and made available to people on this page. Fabric requirements will be shared in advance. You can then use a session (or two, if you like) to complete the project at the same time as others. 
The morning session is 10am - 12.30pm and the evening one is 7pm - 9.30pm.
The cost is £6 per session. This covers use of our sewing machines and equipment as well as threads and hot drinks. 
I will be on hand to help thread machines and offer some advice, but the idea is that experienced sewists help the beginners. Machines and equipment are stored in a dedicated room. Your help in setting up the machines in the morning, and putting away again the evening will be gratefully received.
The tickets are on sale, on a strictly limited, first come first served basis from Eventbrite. Please check you are booking for the correct session before you pay. If you are on means tested benefit or are on a low income please contact me as we may be able to offer a reduced rate. As tickets for each session go on sale they will be advertised on this page.  You can contact us on 020 8421 5544 or 07576 167776.
Please do not post any items for sale on this page. Adverts will be removed.

About this group
Description

This is a group for Sherwoods , other areas Clp members and others to discuss and debate issues in an open and honest way. Some people asked what the clp stands for (Community Likeminded People) We should all respect others views and opinions without any need for abuse or offensive language. We should all be aware of Social Media Policy and we should all make sure all posts are accurate. Any posts going against this will be removed. The assembly within this forum will provide a national forum for anti-austerity views which, while increasingly popular, are barely represented in parliament. 

Group rules from the admins
1.
Be kind and courteous
We're all in this together to create a welcoming environment. Treat everyone with respect and kindness. Healthy debates are natural but abusive language will not be tolerated and posts will be removed.This group is a group to support each other and we will not agree about all issues as we are a diverse group 
Not all members of this group are members of the Labour Party.
2.
No hate speech or bullying
Make sure everyone feels safe. Bullying of any kind isn't allowed, and degrading comments about things such as race, religion, culture, sexual orientation, gender or identity will not be tolerated.
3.
Respect everyone's privacy
Being part of this group requires mutual trust. Authentic, expressive discussions make groups great, but may also be sensitive and private. What's shared in the group should stay in the group.

This is a forum for Sherwoods, other areas CLP. It is for open discussion and organisation 
It has a formal moderation policy as follows

4. By joining this group you are deemed to have read and agreed to these rules
5. All decisions will be decided by the group administrators/moderators. Any individual concerned will be informed and offending posts moderated, the individual will be placed on probation for three months. A further breach
of rules while on probation will result in removal from the group for three months, at the end of this they may apply to re-join the group.
7. All discussions to be conducted in a friendly and polite manner in keeping with the aims and values of Sherwoods
 CLP.
********
8. No admins or moderators can be blocked by any member of the group. If this happens the individual will immediately be removed from the group for three months. At the end of this period they may apply to re-join the group.
********
If screenshots of discussions are posted to other, public, forums then this will result in an automatic suspension as above.




                                                                 Community of Likeminded People

Welcome to the online space for Weston CLP members to help each other keep up to date with what the hell is going on!

By using this Forum you agree to the following.

This is a place for factual information to be shared. Whether that's current affairs, who's who in the Labour party, what training is on offer for members and similar - this is the place for members to help each other work out what the hell is going on!

All members are reminded of the Social Media Policy that forms part of their membership Terms and Conditions of the Labour Party. As do the rules on Safeguarding.

All members should read it and follow the policy and remember that upon becoming a member you agreed to uphold this pledge.

"I pledge to act within the spirit and rules of the Labour Party in my conduct both on and offline, with members and non-members and I stand against all forms of abuse.

I understand that if found to be in breach of the Labour Party policy on online and offline abuse, I will be subject to the rules and procedures of the Labour Party."

This is not the place for the airing of grievances against any other member or officer of the CLP. Any such grievance should be addressed to a member of the Executive Committee directly by email or Private Message.

The admins of this page reserve the right to interpret the Social Media Policy and to delete posts that are in breach of the Social Media Policy or Safeguarding rules of the Labour Party.

Members using this page should refrain from Tagging any CLP Officer unless the matter is particularly urgent or in breach of the above rules.

This is a group for Havant Labour MEMBERS to discuss, organise campaigns and get to know each other. This is a group for the members, by the members, and an attempt to put past troubles behind us and focus on the future with a positive attitude! 
We are all here for the same thing, to get labour seats in Havant so that we can improve the lives of residents.
A variety of admins run this group to make it fair, if you have a problem with anything or anyone, then please message one of us. You can find out who the admin are by looking at the list of members. When we post there is also a shield with a star in it next to our names.
Please read the rules, they're important to keep things running smoothly, if you ignore them consistently after warning, you will be banned from the group.
Do not be afraid to use the report button if you see something inappropriate, admin will discuss any reports and then act accordingly.
Please confirm that you have read the rules and agree to them by commenting on this post with which one you agree with most. If you think anything is missing or vehemently disagree with any of the rules, then please say so and we'll take your input on board.
